table-1612-725.caption: Trails
data: Beginner Area is founded just above the car park
T-Bar 1 is founded just above the car park
Intermediate Area is founded just above the car park
Dome Face is the large open slope above the old cafe and the ski patrol building
Big Mama is the large open slope on the true left of Dome Face, which runs down from the boundary ridge to the base area
Babylon is small open slope that breaks off the main ridge about halfway down, directly above tower-5 of T-Bar 1
Ridge Route is large open slope that is running down from the top main ridge
Julian's Bowl the obvious ‘Y’ shaped bowl below the T-Bar 3 drive station. It is bound by T-Bar 2 lift track on the true left
Headwall is large open slope on the true right side of T-Bar 3 lift line
Sundance Basin is the groomed ski run for T-Bar 3, the slope on the true left of T-Bar 3 lift line
JC’s is the slope from the main ski run on T-Bar 3 to about half way the bowl
Leaper is the slope from about halfway between the large rock buttress in JC's and to the small gullies above the top of T-Bar 2
Aorangi Chutes is the area where the slope is made up of multiple narrow gullies and rocky outcrops above T-Bar 1
Solitude is the slope between the rocky outcrops of Aorangi Chutes and McNulty's Saddle
McNulty's Basin is the groomed trail from top T-Bar 3 through McNulty's Basin
Serpent is the slope below the saddle and the first section of the ridge walk to Bluff Face
Jelly Roll is the slope midsection of the ridge walk to Bluff Face
Pot Belly is located in McNulty’s Basin below the Ridge Walk to Bluff Face, the prominent steep open slope below the summit of 'Allison Peak'
Uli’s Roll is located in McNulty’s Basin below the summit of 'Allison Peak'
Zodiac Traverse is wider open section below the Allison Peak summit
Scorpio is the large open slope in McNulty's Basin on the true right of the prominent rock buttresses, which border onto Libra and the upper part of Bluff Face
Libra is the open slope between the two prominent, parallel rocky ridges, which run down between Scorpio and Bluff Face
Stellar Bowl is the area below the triangular shaped group of rock buttresses on the true right of Libra
Stan’s is the slope directly below the prominent, low buttress between Libra and Bluff Face
Pisces is the slope directly below the lowest rock buttress on the small ridgeline that runs down from Bluff Face true left side
Bluff Face is the large open face on the true left of the ski area with large prominent rock buttresses at the top.
Laurie's Face is the large open slope below the skyline ridge that sweeps down from the true left of Bluff Face
Don't Miss is the slope on the true left of the car park, which is made up of numerous rocks and rocky outcrops of moderate to large size and multiple gullies ranging from very narrow to middle width
The Sphinx is located on the slopes above the snow groomer workshop and the access track

table-1612-427.caption: Title history
data: Became champion when FWA European Union Championship stopped being recognised.
Three way match also involving Scottie Rock.
Masked wrestler J-X defeats Zebra Kid then reveals himself to be Jack Xavier while under suspension.
Championship returned to Zebra Kid when it is revealed that Xavier won the title while suspended.
Zebra Kid forfeits the title by no-showing a scheduled title defence against Flash Barker.
Defeats Flash Barker to win the vacant title after replacing Zebra Kid.
FWA stopped recognising Kincaide as champion on November 19, 2006 when he sided with IPW:UK but was re-recognised for his defence against FWA wrestler Iceman
Defeated Kincaide in a match which FWA would only recognise if Iceman won.
Championship renamed All-England Championship when FWA closes at this event.
Defeated Jonny Moss in the British National Championship final.
